 The Federation Cup, also known as the Fed Cup, is the premier international team competition in women's tennis, organized by the International Tennis Federation (ITF). It was launched in 1963 to celebrate the 50th anniversary of the ITF and is the world's largest annual women's international team sports competition in terms of the number of nations participating. The competition underwent a name change from the Federation Cup to the Fed Cup in 1995. It features national teams representing their countries in a series of matches, with the champion being crowned the best women's tennis team in the world for that year. The Fed Cup aims to promote women's tennis and foster international competition and camaraderie among nations.
